getMemberToken

public String getMemberToken()
returns the identity token of the member that caused this signal to be generated. For instance, in the case of a MessageSignal, this member token would be the sender. In the case of a FailureNotificationSignal, this member token would be the failed member. In the case of a JoinNotificationSignal or PlannedShutdownSignal, the member token would be the member who joined or is being gracefully shutdown, respectively.

Specified by:

returns the identity token of the member

getEventSubType

public GMSConstants.startupType getEventSubType()
Description copied from interface: GroupStartupNotificationSignal
Denote whether Joining member is joining group as part of an entire group startup or not.

Handlers of Join and JoinAndReady notifications may use this information to optimize their handlers to perform differently based on whether all members of group are being started at same time or whether a instance is just joining an already running group.
